## File Structure for AI Optimization

### Frontmatter Metadata (Every File)
```yaml
---
title: "Project Name"
date: "YYYY or YYYY - Present"
status: "Completed | In Production | Prototype | Ongoing"
role: "Your Role"
company: "DECIEM | Personal Project"
parent_initiative: "abnormal-innovation | independent | personal-portfolio"
tags: ["tag1", "tag2", "tag3"]
impact_metrics: ["metric1", "metric2"]
technologies: ["tech1", "tech2"]
context_type: "project_detail | initiative_overview"
context_priority: "critical | high | medium"
---
```

### Content Structure (Consistent Across Files)
1. **Executive Summary** - TL;DR with key achievement
2. **The Problem & Opportunity** - Context, pain points, business impact
3. **Solution Design** - Architecture, approach, innovation
4. **Implementation** - Phased rollout, timeline, process
5. **Results & Impact** - Quantitative + qualitative outcomes
6. **Challenges & Learnings** - What worked, what didn't, lessons
7. **Skills Demonstrated** - Explicit skill callouts

